Iirc, "The customer is always right" was originally tied to giving the customer what they wanted
Like, maybe they wanted something done a specific way, something that was well within reason

But over time it seems to have mutated into this undeserved sense of entitlement, where the customer is NEVER wrong, and if you are unwilling, or unable, to do what they ask, then YOU are in the wrong
We've gotten to this really messed up state of things where customers have ALL the expectations for a business, but the business has ZERO expectations for the customer.
Imagine if customers had to act like how they expect staff to act in order to get the best experience?
